== Overview ==
The '''Uwanabe Kofun''' (宇和奈邊古墳) is a {{ill|zenpō-kōen-fun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft|12=draft}} (keyhole-shaped tumulus) located in {{ill|Nara City|ja|奈良市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県|12=draft|12=draft}}. It is part of the {{ill|Saki Kofun Cluster|ja|佐紀盾列古墳群|1=Saki Tatenami Kofun group|12=draft|12=draft}} and is the easternmost and largest tumulus in the group. built in the mid-5th century, it is managed by the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁|12=draft|12=draft}} as the burial site of {{ill|Princess Yata|ja|八田皇女|12=draft|12=draft}}, daughter of {{ill|Emperor Ōjin|ja|応神天皇|12=draft|12=draft}} and consort of {{ill|Emperor Nintoku|ja|仁徳天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}.

== burial and area ==
The tumulus is a three-tiered structure covered with {{ill|fukiishi|ja|葺石|12=draft|12=draft}}. The first tier was surrounded by a row of {{ill|haniwa|ja|埴輪|12=draft|12=draft}}. While the mound is under the jurisdiction of the Imperial Household Agency, the surrounding moat is maintained by local farmers. Vegetation now covers the surface of the tumulus.

Earlier surveys estimated its length at 255 meters, but a 2020 excavation by the {{ill|Nara Prefectural Kashihara Archaeological Institute|ja|奈良県立橿原考古学研究所|12=draft|12=draft}}, Nara City Board of Education, and the Imperial Household Agency found the tumulus to be 270-280 meters long, surpassing the {{ill|Gosha-jinja Kofun|ja|五社神古墳|1=Gosashi Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}} (267 meters) within the same cluster. This makes it the 12th-largest tumulus in Japan.<ref name="Mainichi20201121" />

Key area:
* Front section width: 129.5 meters
* Rear circular section diameter: 128 meters
* Height: 19.8 meters (rear), 16 meters (front)

