The {{ill|Saki Kofun Cluster|ja|佐紀盾列古墳群|1=Saki Tatenami Kofun group|12=draft|12=draft}} spans the northernmost edge of the {{ill|Nara Basin|ja|奈良盆地|12=draft|12=draft}}. It includes the {{ill|Konabe Kofun|ja|コナベ古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} and other notable Kofuns such as {{ill|Ichiniba Kofun|ja|市庭古墳|1=Ichiniba Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}}. These mounds are surrounded by moats, giving them the appearance of islands within a wetland environment.

