</gallery>

== Geography ==
The {{ill|Saki Kofun Cluster|ja|佐紀盾列古墳群|1=Saki Tatenami Kofun group|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saki Kofun Cluster|13=User:Immanuelle/Saki Tatenami Kofun group|qq=}} spans the northernmost edge of the {{ill|Nara Basin|ja|奈良盆地|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nara Basin|qq=}}. It includes the {{ill|Konabe Kofun|ja|コナベ古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Konabe Kofun|qq=}} and other notable Kofuns such as {{ill|Ichiniba Kofun|ja|市庭古墳|1=Ichiniba Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichiniba Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichiniba Kofun|qq=}}. These mounds are surrounded by moats, giving them the appearance of islands within a wetland environment.

